casebody.data:
DANIEL P. FITZGERALD, Plaintiff and Respondent, v. EDWARD D. VALENTINE, Defendant and Appellant.

Before Freedman, Curtis, and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided June 28, 1873. Wm. W. Peck, and Wm. H. Newman, for appellant. E. Haines, for respondent.

Opinion by Curtis, J. Freedman and Van Vorst, JJ., concurred.

Action for conversion of personal property.

Appeal from a judgment in favor of the plaintiff.

Judgment affirmed.
